model_explanation: the prosodic focus on "BILL" in S1 means Sam didn’t give grapes to others (like Sue), but S2 says he gave grapes to Sue.
the focus in S1 is on "SUE ORANGES," meaning Sam didn’t give oranges to anyone else. S2 contradicts this by saying Rob also got oranges.
the focus on "SUE" in S1 means Sam gave grapes only to Sue, which entails that Sam didn’t give grapes to Ellen or anyone else.
the focus on "TOM APPLES" in S1 entails that Sam gave only apples to Tom and not anything else like grapes.
the focus on "ROB ORANGES" in S1 means oranges were the only thing Sam gave Rob. S2 contradicts by saying Rob also got apples.
focusing on "SUE" in S1 means Sue was the only recipient of grapes, so Tom didn’t get any grapes.
the focus on "ELLEN" in S1 means Ellen was the only one who got bananas, but S2 says Mary also got bananas.
the focus on "ROB BANANAS" means bananas were the only thing Sam gave Rob, so Rob didn’t get oranges.

the focus on "SUE ORANGES" means Sue was the only one who got oranges, so Rob didn’t get oranges.
